<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-9276] Netty4 component allows multiple consumers to bind to the same {host}:{port}</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-9276</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a netty4 tcp consumer on the from route i am able to start multiple instances of this route and there is no &quot;address already in use/ bind exception &quot; being raised by camel, changing the &quot;reuseAddress&quot; to &quot;false&quot; doesnt seem to make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sample config&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;from uri=&quot;netty4:tcp://0.0.0.0:3010?sync=false&amp;amp;textline=true&amp;amp;reuseAddress=false&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;to uri=&quot;log://org.dx.com?level=DEBUG&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Verified and confirm same behavior on OSX and Windows&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12909173">CAMEL-9276</key>
